  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-98955951-7fff-5b29-5ce4-ce1216cec9f7\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed front lightwell would be at odds with the pattern of development in the area and would introduce a discordant feature into the street scene to the detriment of the host building and the terrace it forms part of. As such the proposal is contrary to&nbsp; policy D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan (2021); policy LP1 (Design quality and local character) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).</span></span><br></p>",
    "<p>The rear roof extension, by reason of its excessive size, bulk, design and siting would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development which would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject property and surrounding area. As such, it would be contrary to policies D1 (Londonâ€™s form, character and capacity for growth) and D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP1 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained in the Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).<br></p>",
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a2c26b78-7fff-4d80-c8b2-839a88f111cd\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed development would, by reason of design and placement of fenestration and rooflights would appear as an unsympathetic and incongruous addition to the host building, resulting in a poor design outcome that is of detriment to the character and appearance of the host building, contrary to policy D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP1 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained in the Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).</span></span><br></p>"
  ],
